Final Report

Valeriia Ladyhina & Semyon Kupriyanov

2022-05-21

Introduction

This R Markdown is part of bigger pipeline on analysis of RNA seq data obtained in experiment on effects of different concentrations of antibiotic novobiocin on gene expression in Salmonella enterica subsp. enterica serovar Typhimurium str. 14028S. Analysis was performed on publicly available transciptomics data that can be found here.

Installation of required packages

This part of pipeline includes few different packages, that have been installed on your computer, namely: DESeq2, dplyr, ggplot2, gplots,clusterProfiler, WGCNA, knitr, KEGGREST,stringr.

DESeq2 analysis

For this analysis we used two files: transcript_count_matrix.csv, obtained during previous steps of snalemake pipeline based on StringTie and pheno.csv - file that describes our experimental data.

Next step is normalization of counts and saving of the result into file norm-matrix-deseq2.txt

PCA analysis

At this step we are searching for significant genes

Volcano plot

DEG heatmap

Negative and positive DEG were saved in files negative_deg.txt and positive_deg.txt respectively.

Sample clusterisation to detect outriers

Added to clusters information regarding traits of data set

In this case we will use soft threshold in power 12

Module clustering dendrogram

Significance of modules and their correlation with traits using Spearmans correlation, we will count that resulta are significant if the are >0.7

In our analysis we have five modules that are significant regarding treatment: brown, turquoise, blue, black, yellow; and two regarding time green and red

Plot that reveals relationships between eigengenes and traits
